Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @spring onion{1} then thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Whilst the rice is cooking, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{}, once hot add the @Linda McCartney Vegetarian Meatballs{8} and @cornflour{10%g}, shake the pan to coat the balls in the cornflour. Fry until browned all over, ~{5-7%minutes}, turn every ~{2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and crispy at the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Once the meatballs have coloured add the garlic and cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Next add the @water for the sauce{100%ml}, @hoisin sauce{50%g} and @soy sauce{25%ml}. Rapidly simmer until you have a glossy sauce, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest and half the juice. Divide this between your plates and top with the meatballs and sauce. Finish with the broccoli and a sprinkling of spring onion and @sesame seeds{15%g}. Serve with a wedge of the remaining lime. Enjoy!